    "Given that a single whole-mount (WM) image corresponds to approximately 30 stretched biopsy core images and given the time-and labor-intensive effort of obtaining high-precision annotations of WM images for prostate cancer, we randomly selected 46 radical prostatectomy specimens, for a total of 368 WM images [~ 11,040 biopsy core images with prostatic tissues or 894,240 patch images (512 × 512 pixels, 512 µm, at 10 × by a pixel mapping of ~ 1 µm per pixel] from 136 patients between 2016 and 2019.",
